inn1.comm: Whatever chest infection Lee had has obviously disappeared. Right on target, just outside off stump and shaping away. Two slips in place.
tip and run! Strauss gets off the mark. So does England. Just a nudge to the on side and by the time Hodge tried to swoop in, the run was completed. Meanwhile Hodge stumbles and falls.
No gift to the debutant. Loye receives a yorker first up. Full, furious, and tailing in late, it crashed into the boot. Beaten for pace and by the blockhole length. Welcome to international cricket.
Loye is up and running. International cricket is not so bad after all. Fullish, and he leans forward to drive it straight down the ground. Two runs.
short of length, on the off stump line, defended to point
Short of good length, outside the off stump and shapes away further. Left alone. Bracken is a pretty good ODI bowler, gets the white ball to swing and move away.
closer to the off stump, on a length and bit of bounce and movement away, Strauss withdraws his bat from the line
on the hips, tucked to fine leg
Fuller and it swings in late, on the middle and leg side, Loye attempts to flick it away, the ball bobs away to short fine leg
on the off stump line, punched to mid-off
Just around the off stump, Struass nudges it to cover point, thinks about a single, sees the huge figure of Andrew Symonds rushing across, and settles for a dot ball.
Easy runs. Full and the legs, Lee strays, Loye flicks it past square leg. He doesn't get his front foot across, keeps his feet outside the line and gets two runs
slightly short of length, around the off stump line, carved away to third man region. Lovely looking shot, just a run though.
lands on a length, on the middle stump line, the ball hits the bat, rather than the other way, the bat-handle rotates in the hand, and the ball rolls away to the on side
In the channel outside off stump, Loye shuffles across and lets it sail past him.
beaten! lands on a good length, outside the off stump, and moves away. Strauss flirts and then turns coy; withdraws his bat from the line
on the middle and off stump line, jabbed away to the off side
fuller, on the middle and leg, turned straight to the midwicket.
swing and a miss. 133 kmph. Not that fast but Strauss tried to drill through the line and just knifed through thin air.
134.05 kmph, around the off stump line, pushed to cover point
drifts on to the pads and Strauss pounces on it, works it past square-leg.
fullish, on the middle stump line, Strauss tries to go straight down the ground, it goes to the left of mid-on

Oh ho! what a shot! 34-years of frutstration released into that shot. 150 kmph delivery on the middle stump line, Loye does his special. Goes on the bended knee, and swings it over long leg. Sweeping a fast bowler! He does it in Twenty20, we were wondering whether he can pull it off in the international cricket. Obviously he can and how.
Thwack! On the middle stump line, short of length, Loye short-arm jabs it over square leg! Can we call on all the veterans from the county please.
pitched up, outside off stump and driven past point
Bracken gift-wraps a full toss across, Loye rips open the parcel, sends it crashing to the cover fence
on the stumps, shovelled to midwicket.
beaten! Just outside off stump, slightly short of length, Loye thinks he can cut it away, no luck.
There he goes sweeping. Full and slanted across the off stump, Loye goes forward and tries to sweep it and swing it across, doesn't make contact and it bounds off the pads.
switches to conservative mode again. Solid back foot defence
on a length, on the middle stump line, driven to mid-on
hones in on the off stump, Strauss tries to cut it away, too close to the off stump line, and ends up mistiming it a touch ...
fullish, outside off stump, driven through covers

top-edges a six! Sponsor that part of the blade Strauss! Banged in short and Strauss goes for a pull, is late on that stroke and the ball just flew over the cuckoo's nest. Over fine-leg. He has been dismissed a few times in the Test series going for this stroke.
If you going to sponsor the top edge, then better insure the outside edge. Just in the channel outside the off stump, a lame poke and the ball shaves past the outer edge
on the off stump line, on a length, defended back to the bowler.
Loye goes sweeping. yet again. Not much luck though. Full and outside the off stump, he tries to swing it behind square, gets a inside edge on to his pads.
lands on a length, around the off stump line, just pushed back to the bowler
fullish, just outside the off stump, Loye gets behind the line, nudged to the off side
slower delivery, 119.1 kmph deliver, on the middle stump line, pushed to the right of mid-on. Will retain the strike.
Hmm.... completely unMcGrath like delivery. Short  and on the off stump line, Loye loves it, pulls it through midwicket.
What a shot! That You Tube moment again! Loye's sweep shot. The left foot goes across, outside the off stump, he goes on the bended knee and he swings it behind square leg.

to the classic McGrath line. Boring. Just short of length, on the off stump line. Loye pats it back cautiously as if he is defusing a bomb. McGrath has a few words to say to him. Its nice to see you and such greetings. Yeah right.
that one day dab shot to thirdman. Outside off stump and you know how this one goes.
on the back foot, no violence in Strauss's mind, just defends it away
on the middle and off stump line, nudged back to the bowler.
fullish, outside the off stump line, Loye tries to drill it through the off side, the bat-handle rotates in the hand and the ball bobs away towards mid-off
The intent was to swing it over on field, gets a inside edge and it runs past square leg.
Strauss continues to scrath around. Another attempted cut shot, no contact. Stings Gilchrist's gloves
Deja-vu at Brisbane. This time Struass even tries to charge out, Bracken drags back the length and Struass tries to cut but no luck again.
pushed to point..

Short and wide outside the off stump and Loye flays it away through backward point, this is refreshing cricket. Actually the ball was not there to be cut but he room, got on top of the bounce and played into the ground
swept away top deep backward square, just a single on this occasion
defended on the back-foot
looks like McGrath has found his grove, or is just because Strauss is on strike, anyway good length delivery outside the off stump and Strauss defends it on the front-foot
full on middle and leg, turned straight to the fielder at midwicket
punched off the back-foot and the ball finds the bowler.

And Bracken nails Mal Loye after a run a ball 36. short of a good length delivery, pitched on middle and off and shaping away from the right-hander. Loye plays at it late, more of an afterthought. Ball clips the edge and goes straight to Hayden at first slip.
on the middle and off stump line, Bell gets right behind the line and defends it with a straight bat
line and length delivery, Bell being Bell, gets behind the line and defends it back to the bowler
off the mark. Bracken's angle creates the width and Bell nudges it down to third man for an easy single
good length delivery outside the off stump, Strauss waits for the ball and at the last moment cuts it down to thrid man for a brace
short of a good length delivery, width offered and Strauss cuts it away through point. There is protection in the deep
good length delivery outside the off stump, McGrath has started hitting the coin outside the off stump. Strauss safely plays it down to mid-off
good length and this one came back in a touch. Strauss stays back and works it away on the leg side. Needless to say, the ball went straight to the fielder at midwicket
worked away off the back-foot to the square leg region

Hodge you beauty! short of a good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, innocuous delivery. Strauss having failed playing the drive and the flick goes for the pull and the ball flies away towards midwicket. Hodge there quickly moves across to his left and pulls off a stunner, diving across to his left. He was at full stretch and in the air when he took it and to make it even better he took it with both hands. Amazing effort.
bouncer first up and Joyce ducks under it
good length delivery on the stump and Joyce is made to defend. Wicket maiden
on the middle and leg stump line, defended towards mid-off
Johnson drifts on to the pads and Bell works it away behind square on the leg side
good length delivery on the stumps, Joyce gets behind the line and defends it down

short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, Joyce goes on the back-foot and taps it away towards cover point. Symonds moves across in a flash but the batsmen scamper through for a well judged single
line and length delivery, defended on the back-foot
in the channel outside the off stump, Bell opens the face of the bat and runs it away towards gully
short of a good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Joyce gets right behind the line and defends it down on the off side
driven away towards cover, Symonds at short cover, dives across full length and cuts off the single. This is the kind of support that every bowler dreams off.
forced away towards point, again no run there

short delivery on the middle and leg stump line, not fiery enough to trouble the batsman. Joyce gets right on top of the bounce and pulls it away to through square leg. Fine leg fielder quickly gave up the chase. Excellent timing and placement
in the channel outside the off stump and Joyce leaves it through to the keeper
this one straightened after pitched and Joyce shoulders arms, close call as the ball zips past the stumps
driven off the fornt-foot and the ball goes straight to the fielder at cover
short of a good length and angling across the right-hander. Bell slashes hard at it but fails to make contact. Bit of frustration creeping in I guess.
driven away through backward point, easy two
shot! short of a good length and angling across the right-hander. Bell stands erect on the back-foot, lines it up nicely and drills it through the gap between cover and point. Way to go
good length delivery on the stumps, Bell pushes forward and defends it well
tucked away off the pads to the square leg region, easy single to end the over
good length delivery on the middle and leg stump line, Bell shuffles across a bit and works it away towards midwicket for an easy single
good length delivery, pitched on and around the off stump line and shaping away a touch. Joyce leaves it through to the keeper
and this time he comes down the track but the result is almost the same, Joyce was looking for the drive through cover but the ball rolled away off the inner half of the bat
slightly short and angling across the left-hander. Joyce on the back-foot defending
worked away towards gully, no room for a single there

and McGrath ends Joyce's uneasy stay at the crease with a beauty! short of a good length delivery, this one hit the deck and shaped back in. Joyce was clueless and in the end it was a nothing poke, ball clipped the inside edge and went straight to Gilchrist behind the stumps. That's the end of that and we are back to square one.

goodness me! good length delivery outside the off stump and Bell runs it away towards gully and then came the mix-up. Total mess! Both batsmen meet in the middle and then Bell hesitates quite a bit. He is in two minds whether to run or go back to his end. By this time White had stopped the ball diving across to his left and he flicked the ball lying down all along the ground. Bell tries to run back to the striker's end but White's back-handed flick hits the stumps bang. Bell was nowhere in the picture.
defended on the back-foot
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump and Flintoff leaves it through to the keeper
high bouncer and the umpire is not impressed
driven straight to the fielder at cover point
good length and drifting away, Fintoff goes for the drive but fails to make contact
short of a good length delivery and Flintoff defends it on the back-foot

and the party continue! short of a good length, pitched right in the channel outside the off stump and shaping away late - special delivery for poor mortals and a McGrath usual. Collingwood had no option but to play at it and the edge went straight to Gilchrist behind the stumps. England five down and they are melting like butter on a hot pan.
good length delivery, close to the off stump line and Nixon ends up with an inside edge on to his pad
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump and Nixon pushes it away towards cover point
defended on the back-foot
fuller length delivery on the pads and Nixon works it away behind square on the leg side
beauty to end the over, perfect line and length and the ball shaped a touch. Flintoff is turned inside out and the ball zips past the outside edge
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump and Nixon leaves it through to the keeper. Can't blame him, he is playing out the memo - that's sure
good length delivery outside the off stump and Nixon watchfully drives it straight to Clarke at cover
good length and drifting down the leg side, ball clips the pads and rolls away behind the stumps. Gilchirst had to dive across full length to cut it off  - all in a day's work.
short of a good length delivery, no width offered and Nixon plays it back to the bowler
in the channel and shaping away from the left-hander. Nixon gets behind the line and defends it with a straight bat
worked away towards short midwicket, they think of a single but wisely decides against it.
good length delivery outside the off stump, Flintoff on the back-foot defending. So far he has face 7 balls but he is yet to get off the mark
short of a good length delivery, again right in the channel outside the off stump and Flintoff is made to defend
punched away off the back-foot to the point region, diving stop cuts off the single. Flintoff will have to wait

short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, Flintoff pushes hard at it and the ball flies away off the outside edge, luckily for him and England it went well wide of the diving fielder at gully
pitched up outside the off stump, almost a yorker. Nixon gets behind the line and tamely defends it back to the bowler
short delivery on the stumps, Nixon goes back and pulls it away through square leg
take that! good length delivery outside the off stump, Nixon leans back, quickly gets into a good position and thuds it through the gap between the cover fielder. Good positive shot to break the ice
slightly short and close to the off stump line, Nixon opens the face of the bat and runs it away towards gully

good length delivery outside the off stump, Nixon stays back and drives it away towards cover point. Symonds moves across in a flash but his shy at the bowler's end fails to hit the target. Direct hit would have been interesting
goes for the pull and the ball balloons up off the top-edge but falls safely in the deep, dangerous shot
Johnson once agian drags it short, inviting Flintoff to go after it but on this occasion the big man ducks under it. Wise decision given the situation
good length delivery outside the off stump and Flintoff defends it away towards cover
defended off the back-foot and the ball rolls away towards midwicket
line and length delivery, Nixon gets behind the line and forces it away towards cover
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Nixon says back and defends it down on the leg side
again on the middle and off stump line, no room offered and Nixon is made to defend. Amazing stuff this from McGrath
good length delivery on the stumps and this time Nixon plays it away far, as far as the fielder at midwicket
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, bit of width offered and Nixon cuts it away to third man. Easy two to end the over
good length delivery outside the off stump, Flintoff shuffles across a bit and runs it away behind point
short of a good length and angling across the right-hander. Flintoff gets behind the line and defends it down watchfully
sliced away towards gully, no room for a single there
pitched up outside the off stump, right in the slot and Flintoff goes bang over mid-off, good clean hit and the ball screams away to the fence
Johnson drags it short and Flintoff pulls it away to deep midwicket. Once bounce and straight to the fielder there
good length and angling across, driven straight to the fielder at cover
slightly short and close to the off stump line, cut away off the back-foot to the point region
close to the off stump line and Flintoff nudges it away towards point
good length delivery outside the off stump, Flintoff shuffles back and across and drills it past the fielder at cover
better line and length from Lee. Flintoff stays back and defends it down
Lee drifts on to the pads and Flintoff clips it away through the vacant midwicket region. Long chase from McGrath saves one run

short of a good length delivery, pitched outside the off stump and angling away. Nixon stays back and pokes at it, playing well away from his body. Thick edge and the ball goes straight to Hayden at first slip who snaffles it as clean as a whistle. England six down.
short and wide outside the off stump, Flintoff leans back and cuts it down to third man
good length delivery, angling across and Dalrymple defends it on the back-foot
pitched close to the off stump line and angling across, Dalrymple opens the face of the bat and runs it away towards gully
on the middle and leg stump line, defended straight back to the bowler
ripper! in the channel outside the off stump and this one shaped back in a touch. Dalrymple had no option but to play at it and the ball zips past the outside edge. well bowled
forced away off the front-foot to the cover region, not a convincing shot but he finds the gap and they scamper through for a single
short of a good length delivery and this one nipped back in a touch. Dalrymple jumps into position and plays it down on the off side.
another short of a good length delivery outside the off stump and this one went straight on after hitting the deck. Dalrymple once again lines it up nicely and defends it down
clipped away towards midwicket, slight mix-up going for the single but in the end they make it across comfortably
pitched up and Flintoff finds the fielder at mid-off
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump. Flintoff leans back and cuts late, easy single down to third man
pitched up outside the off stump and Dalrymple defends it down, solid shot
angled in from well outside the leg stump, Flintoff tries to work it away but fails to make contact and the ball rolls away off the pad

short off a good length delivery on the middle and off stump line. Too easy a delivery for a batsman of Flintoff's caliber. He gets right on top of the bounce and pulls it into the ground and the ball races away to the midwicket fence. 100 comes up for England
worked away behind square on the leg side
sliced away towards gully, gets it wide of the fielder there and they scamper through for a single
defended on the front-foot
again worked away behind square, just a single on this occasion
good length delivery and Dalrymple drives it away towards cover
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, Dalrymple gets on his toes and defends it down on the off side
short of a good length delivery, worked away off the the back-foot to the midwicket region
worked away off the back-foot to the midwicket region
defended outside the off stump
good length delivery outside the off stump, little cutter and Dalrymple defends it on the front-foot
short and wide outside the off stump, cut away off the back-foot to the deep backward point region
better line and length and Dalrymple defends it on the back-foot
pitched up wide outside the off stump and Dalrymple is sucked forward into the drive, ball clips the outside edge and flies over the fielder fielder at gully.
defended outside the off stump
played down to silly mid-on, Symonds moves across quickly and cuts off the single
good length delivery outside the off stump and Flintoff taps it away towards point
the big off-cutter, Flintoff plays down the wrong line and ball thuds into the pad, if not for a bid inside edge he was a goner
good length delivery and Flintoff plays it down to mid-off

good length delivery on the middle and off stump line. Flintoff just lines it up nicely and slogs it away to wide long-on. Good clean hit and the ball hits the inside part of the boundary padding. Was signalled as a six but the umpire but then came the camera angles and the third umpire.
fuller length and drifting down the leg side, Flintoff fails to make contact and the ball rolls away off the pad

Hodge pulls off another blinder and England's slump continues! good length and cutting in. Flintoff slogs it away towards midwicket. Hodge in the deep hurtles across to his left, drives across at the last movement and takes it with both hands. Fantastic bit of fielding. England seven down - just three more to go.
defended towards cover
played back to the bowler with a straight bat
worked away on the leg side, no room for a single there
opens the face of the bat and runs it away towards gully
defended on the front-foot
good length delivery outside the off stump and the edge is produced but the ball rolls down to third man
short rising deliverty and Tremlett sways away from the line
And Lee troubles the 6 foot 8 gaint with a nasty bouncer. This one nipped back in a long away and Tremlett was caught on the wrong foot, ball clips the outside edge and pops up towards point
worked away off the back-foot to the square leg region, not a convincing shot but they cross over for a single
worked away towards gully, no room for a single there
bit of width offered and Dalrymple cuts it away through point
worked away off the back-foot to the midwicket region
defended outside the off stump, ball rolls away towards gully
good length delivery on and around the off stump line, Tremlett gets behind the line and defends it back to the bowler
in the slot outside the off stump and Tremlett drills it through extra cover for four, Good looking shot that
on the middle and leg stump line, on the shorter side and Tremlett defends it down on the leg side
good length delivery outside the off stump
bouncer to end the over and Tremlett ducks under it
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven away towards cover
fuller length delivery outside the off stump and Dalrymple drives it past the fielder at cover, nicely opened the face of the bat at the point of impact to get the placement right
short rising delivery outside the off stump and Dalrymple leaves it through to the keeper
short of a good length delivery and this time he cuts it away through point
even better! good length delivery outside the off stump and Dalrymple lofts it away to the cover fence. Good hit through the line and he comfortably cleared the fielder inside the circle.
turned away off the back-foot to the square leg region, easy single to end the over
good length delivery outside the off stump, Dalrymple gets well forward and defends it down watchfully
fuller in length and Dalrymple drives it hard into the track, ball bounces over the bowler and they scamper through for a single
cut away off the back-foot to the point region
good length delivery, driven off the front-foot to the long-off region
in the channel outside the off stump and Tremlett plays it away towards gully
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Dalrymple defends on the back-foot
steered away off the back-foot and the ball rolls away through gully
good length and angling across, played straight to the fielder at gully.
pitched up and angling across and Dalrymple drives it down to long-off.  Dalrymple is showing some character here

Bracken strikes! well disguised slower delivery. Tremlett tries to open the face of the bat and run it down to third man but fails miserably. Just the thinnest of edges and the ball flies straight to Gilchrist behind the stumps. Eight down - two more go.
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump and Lewis leaves it through to the keeper
off-cutter and Dalrymple ends up playing down the wrong line. Loud shout for lbw turned down, Hawkeyes shows that the ball would have clipped the leg stump.
good length delivery on the stumps, defended
fuller length delivery and Dalrymple is beaten once again, probably an inside edge onto the pad
goes for the drive outside the off stump and the ball salis through to the keeper
yorker on the stumps and once again Dalrymple is beaten all ends up. End of a good over
edged away behind the stumps on the off side, Hayden at wide first slip fails to time his jump properly and the ball rolls down to third man, looked like he got a touch on it
good length delivery on the pads and Dalrymple clips it away through midwicket
again worked away on the leg side for an easy single
good length delivery, angling across and Lewis drives it away towards cover

got'm! and once again it's the slower ball that does the trick. Low fulltoss on the middle and off stump line. Lewis jams his bat down, probably he thought it was the yorker. Ball hits the bottom part of the bat and spoons up straight back to the bowler.
pushed past the fielder at point and Anderson is off the mark.
floated on the off stump line, defended off the front foot&
Cut and miss. Close to the off stump line, Anderson thinks he can cut ala Lara and is beaten
realises he is just Anderson, leaves this delivery outside off stump all alone
tossed up on the middle stump line, Anderson sweeps it past square-leg. Will get two.
perfect forward defence. Head over the ball and all that jazz
Fullish, outside off stump, driven to deep cover.
full in a length, just outside the off stump, Anderson leans forward, pushes it out into the cover region.
Bouncer! Bracken digs it in, Anderson withdraws his bat from the line and the ball just whizzes past his face. Smell the leather!
slightly slower in pace, on the middle stump line, Anderson doesn't move his feet, is keeping that while he bowls, just shovels this one into midwicket
sailing through the channel outside off, Dalrymple tries the one-day dab shot, misses.
slips that down leg side. Wide called.
top spinner on the middle and leg, tucked towards square-leg. The camera pans to Vaughan and Collingwood sitting outside. Some of the crowd cheer, some jeer...
floated on the off stump line, lapped around the corner, Anderson almost turns blind for the second run, and is sent back. Wise move. He just about dives into the crease.
googly but again down the leg side
slides this one again on the legs, worked towards square-leg for a single
floated on the leg stump line, flicked to right of Michael Clark midwicket who dives to make the stop

There you go. England shot out for 155. The awful summer continues. Short of length, outside the off stump, Dalrymple could have pulled it anywhere but he decides this is the time to end the misery and hits it right at the throat of long on.

inn2.comm: Starts off with one in the channel outside off, Gilchrist shuffles across, covers the off stump and shoulders arms.
on the hips, Gilchrist waits for the ball to arrive, works his wrists, tucks it away to fine leg. Australia are off.
on the thigh, bobs away off the thigh pad, towards square-leg and they will take a run.
again on the legs, another leg bye. He is operating from round the stumps and, at the moment, is spearing them down.
banging in at short of length, dabbed away to the off side
again on the legs, this can't be the plan, nudged past in front of square leg
good delivery to start off. Fullish, tailing in late, at middle stump line, Hayden arrests his front foot movement, drives it towards mid-off
No swing this time, ends up as a overpitched delivery, on middle and off stump line, again driven to mid-off. The mid-off is standing pretty straight for Hayden
slants across the off stump, full in length, Hayden leans forward, shoulders arms
on the hips, Hayden eases back, punches it through midwicket region
Anderson hurls if full and fast, around the off stump line, driven to mid-off
There we go. Hayden frees his arms. Didn't take long. Fullish, on the stumps, Hayden decides that should disappear, biffs it across, over midwicket, one bounce over the ropes.
from round the stumps, just in the channel outside off, Gilchrist moves across, and lets it fly past him
lands on a good length, outside off, comes in a touch, Gilchrist opens the bat-face, runs it to point
slightly short of length, comes in towards the off stump, Gilchrist gets behind the line, head over the ball, left elbow high and defends solidly. Hmm....
lands on middle, on a length, slips down towards the pads, Gilchrist tries to dab it away, doesn't make contact and the ball rolls off the pads.
around the off stump line, continues with the general theme of the over, Gilchrist moves back, pushes it out into the cover region.
Ala Harmison. Way outside off stump.
closer to the off and from a length, Hayden lets it sail into the 'keeper's gloves.
shorter and width outside off but Hayden turns into a monk and shoulders arms
fuller but again well outside off stump, Hayden doesn't flirt at it.
wide down the leg side. All over the shop.
short of length and again bit of width outside the off stump, left alone.
again angling away, Hayden leans forward, and lets it go past him.
And again.
upper  cut over slips! Gilchrist breaks free! Slightly short of length and outside off stump, Gilchrist throws his blade at it and it flies off the top edge, over the slips.
again from round the stumps, honing in on the off stump, defended back down the track, the bat came down at an angle and the ball rolls away towards the leg side
beaten! In the zone outside off, holding its line and Gilchrist has a poke at it.
goes wide the crease, full and on the middle stump line, Gilchrist goes back, turns it past square-leg.
back to over the wickets for Hayden. Just whistling through the corridor, Hayden lets that one go through as well.
Hayden had enough of shouldering arms. Walks down the wicket, Lewis drags back his length, and pushes it outside off, Hayden adjusts to cut it past point
back to round the stumps. On the middle and off, again that bat comes down in an angle, the bat-face shut, and the ball rolls away to the leg side.
Hayden loves walking. Again he is down the track, Anderson bangs it in, on the hips, Hayden is cramped for room and tries to jab it away to the on side, is hit on the thigh pad.
on the middle and off stump line, slanting across, pushed to the off side
slips down leg side.

Again that walk down the track. Again the shortening of the length by the bowler but this time Anderson pushes it outside off and that allows Hayden attempt a cut, and the ball flies to the right of thirdman
huge shout for lbw. Lands on a length, on the middle stump line, Hayden shuffles across, and is trapped on the pads. But it is going over off stump line.
on a length, just outside the off stump, Gilchrist opens the  bat-face, runs it past point

Anderson takes a very good running catch at long leg. It was banged in slightly short of length, on the middle stump line, Gilchrist goes for the pull, ends up skying it high and Anderson runs to his right and holds on to a smart catch.
Full and on the middle and off stump line, Hayden drives it back to the bowler
Super shot! Full and around the off stump line, Hayden leans forward and unfurls a lovely square-drive.
fuller, outside off stump, Hayden goes hard at it, too much bottom-hand, and the ball rolls towards mid-off
pushed across Hayden who shoulders arms.
on a length, around the off stump line, Hodge gets behind the line to defend. He averages just around 15 in the ODIs.
back-of-length delivery, outside off stump, Hodge pushes  it, bat away from his body, towards point

Hodge's one-day travails continue. Full and on the middle and leg, it holds its line a touch, Hodge looks to turn it the on side, gets a outer edge and it flies to point where Darlymple takes it right in front of his face. Australia lose their second wicket. No Ricky Ponting today. Under slight pressure
Beauty! Fullish, outside off and it holds its line again, Clarke lunges forward, late, and is beaten
shaves past off stump. Landed outside off, came back in, Clarke shoulders arms and the ball just whizzes past the stick.
fullish outside off, swatted away through extra cover
on the off stump line, full in length, Hayden leans forward, pushes it out towards mid-off
In the channel outside off stump, left alone. Replays reveal that it was huge no ball.
lands on a length, on the off stump line, shaping away slightly, defended off the front foot
fuller and outside off, pushing Clarke across who leans towards the line and decides to leave it alone
And again. End of a pretty good over. England are keeping it tight here.
slanted across Hayden, left alone.
nippy delivery, on the middle and leg, this one shapes back in a touch and Hayden is cramped for room. The ball bobs away off the thigh pad.
Back to outside off stump, angling away, left alone
The routine continues. After a delivery outside off, this one is on the middle and leg, and holdings its line and again Hayden has no room to work around with. And the ball thuds into the thigh pad
no prize for guessing where this one went. Full and outside off, angling away
for variety, he takes this one away as well, left alone. Another good tight over from Anderson.
on the off stump line, Clarke leans forward and pats it to the off side.  Australia need another 122 runs.
Lewis pings the outside-off channel, Clarke, as usual, comes forward, sees the line and shoulders arms. Test match cricket on.
Fullish, on the off stump line, defended away. Australia continue to play it cautiously. Even the England fielders must be surprised.
on the hips Clarke goes back, dabs it to fine leg

Oh ho! Hayden falls. Again that walk down the track, this time its fatal. Lewis drags back the length and hurls it at the body, Hayden pulls it to long leg into the waiting palms of Anderson. Three down! Game on?
Short of length, outside off, Clarke forces it through the off side ring, Flintoff gives the chase. 38 for 3.
a bouncer! Wide called for the height. Too short and it sails harmlessly over Clarke's head. Good intent as Clarke's first movement is to get forward.
lands on a length, on the off and middle, defended to the on side
whistles through the zone outside off. left alone and it thuds into Nixon's gloves
left alone again. Bell goes across to have a animated chat with Flintoff. Hopefully ,he has convinced his skipper about his run out
on a length, on the middle stump line, holding its line, worked past square-leg
slightly short of length, on the leg and middle, whipped in front of square-leg and they run hard and will get two.
full and on the off stump line, Symonds leans forward and pats it gently towards cover
nice probing delivery, just outside off stump, Symonds thinks about playing it but decides against it.
again that off stump line, pushed out to cover region
Enough is enough, says Symonds and drills this past point. Fullish and outside offstump, Symonds just transfers his immense weight back and slices it past point.

Revenge! Lewis sends Symonds packing. Again full and outside off stump line, looked pretty similar to the previous delivery but a tad wider, and Symonds throws his bat at it and gets a thick edge. Nixon goes airborne and takes it in front of first slip. Surely, hopefully for all of you out there desperate for a contest, game on!
shout for a catch behind! Off the thigh pad. Slipping down the leg side, and attempted flick doesn't make contact and Nixon dives to his right to gather that one.
on the off stump line, dabbed to point
full and well outside off, left alone
sailing through full outside that off stump line, they have continued pinging that line, left alone.
Clarke leans forward, towards the line, pushes it out to cover region. Flintoff at mid-off has a chat with the bowler.
Just short of Collingwood at gully. Slightly short of length, around the off stump line, holds its line, a unsure Clarke pushes hard at it and gets an outside-edge but ....
pushes that one full and well outside offstump, inviting a loose drive but Hussey resists.

beauty! oh but it is a no ball. Lands on a length, on the off stump line and shapes away, Hussey had to play at it and is beaten. But to his credit , he pushes his bat inside the line and doesn't follow the ball.
outside off stump line, dabbed away to point
Fullish, on the off and middle stump line, tapped away to off side
slips down leg side, glanced to fine leg
hits the deck short of length, outside off stump and it shapes away further, punched through cover point
just outside off stump, on a length, left alone.
well outside off stump, Clarke guides it to left of point
fullish, on the middle and leg, pushed to mid-on
full and slanting away, Hussey tries to ping the gap in cover and is beaten
on the middle stump line, the bat comes down straight and he pats it back to the bowler
on the off stump line, Hussey remains wonderfully side-on, pushes it out to cover
fuller, just outside off stump, Hussey leans forward, opens the bat-face, runs it past point.
right away on target. In the zone outside off stump, left alone.
on the off stump line, punched back towards the left of Flintoff who flings himself to make the stop.
Fuller and outside off and Clarke is caught at the crease a bit, drives and it goes off the outer edge through cover.
banged in short, outside off stump, Clarke presses back to pull it over midwicket. Doesn't get it on the sweet spot but sweet enough for it to almost reach the ropes.
Just outside off stump, angling away, 144 kmph, Hussey lets that one sting Nixon
And again. Good start from Flintoff.
hits the deck short of length, gets bounce and Clarke shapes for a pull, is beaten for pace and bounce and that ball thuds into his tummy. Ouch.
way outside off, lost control at the release. It appeared as if he was trying to for a outswinger there.
on the middle stump line, defended compactly to the on side.
goes for the yorker this time. Fullish and on the middle stump line, stabbed back at the bowler. Tremlett makes the stop, threatens to throw it back at the stumps.
on the middle stump line, fuller, worked to midwicket
length-delivery, just outside off and holding its line, Clarke is squared-up a touch, pushes it out to point.
short of a good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Hussey judges the bounce to precision and leaves it through to the keeper.
good length delivery but well wide of the off peg, Hussey shoulders arms
good length and close to the off stump line but Hussey reads it well and once again leaves the ball through to the keeper. They are in on hurry.
and again. Good length and angling across the left-hander. Hussey shoulders arms
short of a good length delivery, in the channel outside the off stumpand Hussey plays it away towards point
fuller length delivery outside the off stump and Hussey drives it away behind point, takes on the fielder in the deep and he comfortably comes back for the second.
good length delivery on the middle and leg stump line, Clarke stays back and works it away towards midwicket. Straight to the fielder
slightly short and shaping away late. Clarke pushes forward and ends up with a thick edge down to third man.
left alone outside the off stump. Hussey playing the waiting game
bit of width offered outside the off stump and Hussey glides it away towards gully, one more added to the total - they need another 90 runs to wrap this up.
good length delivery outside the off stump. Clarke pushes forward and taps it away towards point
line and length delivery on the middle and off stump line. Clarke gets well forward and defends it straight back to the bowler. Another tidy over from Tremlett comes to an end.
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven away towards cover
surprise bouncer and Hussey was caught on the wrong foot, in the end the ball angled away from the left-hander and Hussey safely swayed away from the line. Too high says the square leg umpire
left alone outside the off stump
short of a good length delivery, once again Hussey is not interested
good length delivery outside the off stump, Hussey shoulders arms. Is this the right approach - well time will tell
short of a good length delivery, pitched close to the off stump line and angling across. You guessed it - again left through to the keeper
well,  well. short of a good length and angling in but not enough to make Hussey play at it.
good length delivery outside the off stump, not to be left behind, Clarke too shoulders arms
Tremlett drifts on to the pads and Clarke nicely tucks it away behind square on the leg side
Tremlett gets the ball to swing a fair distance but he needs a new radar. Way down the leg side. 'That's a wide' is the verdict
good length delivery outside the off stump, Hussey gets behind and defends it away towards cover
left alone outside the off stump.
good length and angling across. Finally Hussey decides to play a shot, good looking drive but the ball goes straight to the fielder at cover.
bouncer to end the over and Hussey ducks under it
short of a good length delivery, slanting away from the righ-hander. Clarke get under the bounce and cuts it away in the air and well over the fielder at gully
good length delivery outside the off stump, no shot offered
again shoulders arms to perfection and the ball sails through to the keeper at good pace. 142 kmp to be excat
hit on the pads trying to flick it away through midwicket
quick bouncer and Clarke had no option but to duck under it
left alone outside the off stump
good length delivery outside the off stump and Hussey leaves it through to the keeper. So what's new.
worked away off the pads to the backward square leg region
off-cutter. Clarke ends up with an inside edge on to the pad and the ball rolls away on the off side, just enough room and they steal a single
slightly short and outside the off stump, for a moment it looked like he was going to play a shot but finally he leaves the ball through to the keeper.
again left alone outside the off stump
finally! short and wide outside the off stump, this time even Hussey couldn't resist going after it. Rocks back nicely and cuts the ball through point. Refreshing shot

good length delivery outside the off stump. Clarke gets well forward and drives it through the gap between the cover fielders. No stopping that - Slowly but steadily this game is slipping away - England desperately need a wicket
good length delivery outside the off stump, hint of swing and Carke leaves it through to the keeper

pitched up outside the off stump, Clarke leans forward and thuds it straight back down the track to the long-off fence. Not a pretty looking shot but he got enough bat on it to beat the fielder at mid-off
good length delivery on the middle and leg stump line, Clarke stays back and clips it away behind square on the leg side. This is excellent cricket from the young man
off the pads and the ball rolls away towards square leg, they scamper through for a single
good length and drifting down the leg side, Clarke fails to make contact but the ball rolls away off the pad to short fine leg. End of a good over for Australia
good length delivery outside the off stump, defended outside the off stump.
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, Clarke goes for the cut but fails to make contact. Too close to cut
good length delivery outside the off stump. Clarke pushes forward and defends it down watchfully

take that! good length and in the channel outside the off stump, nothing wrong with the delivery. Clarke stretches forward and across, gets close to the line of the ball and drives it through cover. Perfect timing and the placement was even better
tucked away off the back-foot to the square leg region, another good over for Australia comes to an end
good length delivery outside the off stump, defended on the front-foot

and he strikes! good length and drifting down the leg side, Clarke follows the ball in a effort to clip it down to fine leg but fails to make solid contact. Not sure if there was any wood involved, hard to say from here. The keeper and the bowler were convinced and so was the umpire. That's the wicket they were looking for - Australia five down.
bouncer first up and White ducks under it. Lewis is pumped up and he lets White know what his plans are for the evening.
another bouncer and White ducks under this one too.
good length delivery outside the off stump and White defends it down safely
short of a good length delivery, defended on the back-foot and the ball rolls away towards point.
short delivery on the middle and off stump line and Hussey pulls it away through midwicket
good length delivery outside the off stump and Hussey leaves it through to the keeper
again left alone outside the off stump
short of a good length and Hussey is troubled by the extra bounce, ball clips the glove and rolls away behind the stumps on the off side
short delivery outside the off stump and Hussey pulls it away well wide of the fielder at midwicket. Australia need another 57 runs. England need 5 more wicekts. Any bets?
make that 55. Clipped away off the pads to the vacant square leg region, runs hard for the first run and comfortably comes back for the second
worked away behind square for an easy single
good length delivery on the stumps and Hussey defends it off the front-foot
with the keeper standing up Lewis bangs it in short. Hussey leaves it through and Nixon had to jump high to collect the ball, just about got there in time. Excellent take
short of a good length and drifting down the leg side, ball clips the pad and runs down to short fine leg
in the channel outside the off stump, White on the back-foot defending
punched away off the back-foot to the cover region. End of a fine spell from Lewis.

and he starts off with Jaffa! Good length delivery, pitched close to the off stump line and shaping away. Hussey is sucked forward and the ball goes through to the keeper. Loud pleading appeal turned down. Anderson is not happy.
steered down to third man and they cross over for an easy single
slightly short and slightly wide, White unleashes a ferocious slap and the ball screams away to the backward point fence. Try stopping that

Anderson strikes back for England and the see-saw battle continues. Good length delivery and this one nipped back in off the deck. White plays across the line and the ball thuds into the pad. Loud shout and on this occasion the umpire adjudicates in favour of the bowler.
bit too straight and Lee flicks it away through square leg, off the mark first ball
left alone outside the off stump
Bouncer and he ducks under it
short of length, around off stump, dabbed to point
Another bouncer, Lee evades that one.
short of length, outside off, dabbed away to thirdman
slanted across, outside off stump, left alone
Fullish, just outside off stump, Lee goes back and across, square-drives it to deep point. Pleasing stroke.
Lovely delivery. Lands on the off stump line, shapes away, Hussey is bit late in pulling out of the shot, just about manages it
on the stumps, nudged to the on side
nip-backer. Lands on a length, on the off stump line, jags back in, Lee stabs at it, gets a inside edge on to his thigh

Again Lee is troubled by the in-coming delivery. Lands on the seam around off stump line and comes back in, Lee tries to force it off the back foot, gets his bat down the wrong line and the ball threads the bat and pad gap and whistles through to Nixon.
fuller and on the leg and middle, clipped past square leg
Top-edges a six! That one flew right into the stands. Banged in short and Hussey goes for the pull and it almost crashes into a lady standing in the aisles. She just about jumps out of the way!

The ball just rolled towards square-leg, was still inside the 30-yard circle but they complete two runs! Awesome running between the wickets. Dabbed to that region and by the time the man from the deep rushes in, they take two.
Pushed across Hussey, who withdraws his bat from the line and watches it sail into Nixon's gloves
beaten! On a length, just around the off stump and shapes away, Hussey tries to punch it down the ground and the ball shaves past the outside edge
fuller and a tad wider outside off, Hussey leans forward, covers the line and lets that one go through to the 'keeper
None of them come into play as this one slips down the leg side. Costly. Another 32 runs to get.
back of length, outside off stump, Lee pushes it,  bat away from the body, to point.
swing and a miss. Short of length and well outside the off stump, Lee tries to cut but doesn't make any contact. The camera pans to Hussey, no emotion there.

hones in on the middle stump, Lee doesn't quite get behind the line, just pushes it away back down the track. The camera now pans to Aussie dressing room. Emotions there. Tense and their eyeballs fixed at the action in the middle.
fuller and touch outside off stump, Lee leans forward, gets close to the line, square-drives and gets it past point.
Fullish, outside off stump, Hussey doesn't quite lean forward fully, drives and it runs off a thickish outside edge, to thirdman region.
banged in short of length, it rears up chest-high, Lee hops up, gets on top of the bounce and remains side-on, dabs it away to the off side.

Another one that kicks up from just short of length, Lee hops but this one comes in at the body, he fends at it ungainly - the bottom-hand is taken out, and he just pushes his bat out like a shield and it bobs away towards short leg.
After two probing deliveries at the body, Flintoff hurls this one short and well outside off stump, Lee drills it through the off side ring. 3 valuable runs.
This one is way outside off.  wide called. He was trying to push it across Hussey but ended up slanting it too wide
straighter and fuller, on the middle and leg, too straight and Hussey tucks it behind square-leg
Flintoff gets back to the routine. At the ribs, Lee jumps up, again the bottom-hand is out and he dabs it away towards shortleg. There is a man at leg gully now.
This one is just outside off, kicking up from short of length, Lee pushes it out to point
from round the stumps, short and wide, that won't help England, slapped to deep point

fuller, outside off stump, drawing Lee forward - he has been hopping against Flintoff, so this is a good move from the bowler - but Lee does well, immediately leans forward, pushes it out to cover region
Ah! back to the ribs. dabbed away. This is rivetting stuff.
Lee leans forward to a delivery angling in, turns it fine down leg side. Will get two.
THat one screams over slips. Full and outside off stump, Lee tries to swing it to Melbourne and gets a thick outside edge and away she flies

Banged in short of length, Lee goes for the pull shot but doesn't get a touch. An interesting over comes to an end. He pinged the ribs and slipped in a few fuller-length deliveries. Produced an edge but no luck
Hussey continues to be rock solid. Flintoff tries to melt him outside off stump with a teasing delivery but Hussey is unmoved.
beats him rightaway. Fullish on the off stump line, and Hussey goes for a drive but Flintoff has the key, bends the delivery away .
Hussey gets right behind this one - around the off stump line- pushes it out to cover region
hits the deck around back of length, just outside off stump and Hussey goes back, shoulders arms.
Caressed to cover drive! Fullish, outside off stump, Hussey leans forward to drive it through extra cover. 14 runs to win.
In the channel outside off stump, Hussey is not interested in the program, lets that sail past him
Whack! Slapped to point boundary. Short and wide, Lee goes back and across and spanks it flat over point and it goes one bounce into the ropes. Now only 10 runs left.
on a length, around off stump line, holds its line, Lee adjusts to that straightening and nudges it away to the off side.

Banged in short, at the ribs, Lee fends it away in front of him and is trying to find where it landed. Meanwhile Hussey spots a run in it and calls Lee over. They rush across and make it rather easily at the end.
Tremlett checks whether Hussey can play a pull shot. Gets a positive answer. Banged this one short and Hussey pulls it over midwicket
hits the deck short of length, it screams up, Lee backs away a touch, stabs at it and the ball goes off a inside edge, just past the stumps.
In the corridor outside off stump, Hussey is in the bedroom, lets that go past him
Just four more needed. One stroke away. Short and just outside off stump (Flintoff is bowling from round the stumps) and Hussey rocks back and pulls it down and it screams to the midwicket boundary.
yorker-length delivery, on the stumps, driven to mid-off

That's it. All over. Fullish and just outside off stump, Hussey leans forward, square-drives it past point where Collingwood is beaten and the man at deep point rushes to his right, flings himself near the ropes and the ball evades him. Despairing drive, so close, yet so far. The story of the day as far as England are concerned. Australia register yet another win, do they ever get bored of it?!
